Where Revenue Actually Leaks (The Big Picture)When a company misses its revenue targets, leadership usually looks for a single, massive culprit. They blame a missed enterprise deal, a bad quarter from the sales team, or a sudden drop in marketing budget.But in reality, revenue leakage is rarely one big mistake.It is a death by a thousand cuts. It is the cumulative effect of tiny, invisible operational gaps across your entire go-to-market (GTM) tech stack and process pipeline.The Reality of the "Revenue Bucket"Imagine your revenue engine as a bucket. You keep pouring more leads, more budget, and more headcount into the top, expecting it to fill up. But if the bucket has 15 microscopic holes drilled into the bottom, it will never fill—no matter how fast you pour.   [ Marketing / Sales / CS Inputs ]
